# GitHub Workflow

- **Repository:** `morphingcoffee/GameLauncher` (public)
- **Prefer GitHub MCP** for issues, PRs, project board, and Actions status before shell fallbacks
- **Link work to issues:** branch names like `phase-N/short-desc`; PR body includes `Closes #N`
- **Project board:** [Game Launcher Roadmap](https://github.com/users/morphingcoffee/projects/1) — user project **#1** (`morphingcoffee`). **Every new launcher issue must be added to this project** — see `github-task-creation` skill. **Track progress via project Status field only** — do not post implementation-status comments on issues. **Mandatory lifecycle:** user asks to work on #N → run `./tools/dev/github-project-status.sh N "In progress"` as the **first action** (before code); PR opened (`Closes #N`) → `"In review"` immediately after `gh pr create`; merge → `Done`. Never leave an issue in Backlog while working on it; never leave it In progress after opening a PR.
- **Before commit/push:** follow `secret-hygiene` skill; run `tools/dev/scan-secrets.sh`
- **Secrets:** PAT only in macOS Keychain (`security`); inject via `tools/dev/github-pat-from-keychain.sh` or `tools/dev/open-cursor-with-github.sh` — never in project config files; global MCP config at `~/.cursor/mcp.json` uses `${env:GITHUB_PAT}` only
